{
  "stem": "9262.3",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "There wasn't anything about being anti-Semitic at the time.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So they couldn't believe that these Germans were like that-- murderers, sadistic.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And Polish Jewish women were taken from the street.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They had to clean up the snow, clean up the streets, which was done before the war by Poles who were-- who got paid from the council to do the cleaning, the street cleaning.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Here it was done by Jews.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We're talking about now September 1939, when the Germans marched into Poland, into Lodz.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And there was snow about.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, snow fell later.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The snow fell after September, October, sort of later October.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And of course, the rain.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And in Poland, the water cistern get overflowed because they haven't got the drainage, and they have a lot of sand.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So there's spillage in the street, sandy and sloshy.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Yes, as I said, very, very primitive it was.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Now, Jewish shops were confiscated.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Before the Germans even had a chance to come and take anything away the Poles were looting.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They came into the Jewish shops, and they took everything.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And then when the Germans, the ethnic Germans, found out what the Poles were doing, they got hold of the Poles, took away what the Poles have robbed, then came back with the Germans, the German SS units, to try to get the last residue what was left.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And of course, what they couldn't find, they used to go with the bayonet and poke it around in the pillowcases to see if anything was hiding there or just stick their bayonets anywhere around to find out if anything-- sometimes they found, and sometimes they didn't.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So those who didn't, they give them a good beating.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
